Module1 Search for cancer hallmarks

Patipark Kueanjinda

October 10, 2018; last modified on June 9, 2020

Call necessary R packages.

Download all data tables.

Data pre-processing steps Removel white space in the columns in GR50 table

Modify names of CCA cell lines obtained from CSV table to meet conventional names

To compare expression level, we divided cell lines into 2 groups by their response to comprehensive drugs (CCA1 and CCA2). Average (log2TMP) of gene expression level per gene per cell line would be calculated and duplicates were eliminated. Genes with average expression levels less than 50th quantile were removed.

Number of genes post-processing

[1] 13390

In general, gene expression levels are reported as the fold-change of expression level of cases compared to controls. In this study, however, the controls were defined as median expression level across all CCA cell lines. (Normal cholangiocyte gene expression data were not included.) Hence, fold-change expression level of genes in each cell line was calculated from comparison of the expression level of the gene of a cell line to median expression level of the same gene across all cell lines.

Now, we converted from log2TPM to median-centered expression level.

In the next step, we wanted to use GSEA for pathway analysis. In general, GSEA requires input data including gene expression levels from A compared to B. Thus, we defined A as CCA1 group (n = 6) and B as CCA2 group (n = 9), according to analysis in Figure 3A. Because median value is less affected by ouliers and represented nearly true value of the population, we calculated median expression level of genes in each subtype and converted to fold-change expression level of genes (FC = median A/ median B).

Because we were also interested in cell line-organ similarity, we created organ similarity category.

Drug sensitivity determination

GR50 values (in log10 format from Figure 2A) were used determine whether the cell lines were sensitive or resistant to a particular drug. Regardless of distribution of GR50, median GR50 of the population was calculated for a particular drug.

Identification of significnat cancer hallmarks using GSEA

We next asked what pathways were enriched in: 1. CCA subtype 1 2. Individual drug sensitive 3. Liver-like 4. Individual cell line compared to whole population

To perform GSEA, we needed to convert from gene expression level (herein log2[TPM]) to fold-change expression level compared to specific the control group. Hence, for each question the control group was: A. CCA subtype 2 B. Individual drug resistant C. Pancreas-like D. median expression levels of genes across all cell lines

Calculate fold-change expression level of drug sensitive over drug resistant group (2-B) We needed a) log2TMP expression level data and b) individual drug response data.

Calculate fold-change expression level of CCA1 over CCA2 group (1-A) We needed a) log2TMP expression level data and b) CCA subtype identification

`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

Calculate fold-change expression level of liver-like over pancreas-like group (3-C) We needed a) log2TMP expression level data and b) organ similarity identification

`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

Calculate fold-change expression level of individual cells over population (4-D) We needed a) log2TMP expression level data and b) TPM.z

Save fold-change of expression levels data table
